Competition from established coffee shops: The coffee shop will face competition from established coffee shops in the area, which may have a loyal customer base and a reputation for quality.

High overhead costs: Starting a coffee shop requires a significant investment in equipment, inventory, and staffing. The high overhead costs may make it difficult for the coffee shop to turn a profit.
Difficulty in attracting customers: In a highly competitive market, it may be difficult for the coffee shop to attract customers and establish a loyal customer base.
Difficulty in finding qualified staff: Finding qualified staff to work in a coffee shop can be challenging, especially in a highly competitive market.
Difficulty in maintaining quality: In a highly competitive market, it may be difficult for the coffee shop to maintain a high level of quality in its products and services.
